<p><strong>A sign of the times soon to be sorted</strong></p>
<p>Following concerns raised with the bus timetable realtime system problems at Lochee High Street bus stop, opposite Bank Street, I made a few inquiries.</p>
<p>I have been advised that this has been reconfigured based on an expected opening date of August 18. This didn’t happen. So, to avoid giving out wrong information on the predicted bus times’ display, it was thought best to turn off the realtime for a couple of weeks until work was completed.</p>
<p>The shelters will be removed and relocated during the first week of September. Power supply to the new location will be organised as quickly as possible. </p>
<p>I am pleased that people have noticed that the realtime display is currently unavailable as it demonstrates the value of the system to bus passengers.<strong> Councillor Alan Ross.</strong></p>
