<p><strong>Innocent until proven guilty</strong></p>
<p>I’d like to applaud Martel Maxwell upon her “innocent until proven guilty” article.</p>
<p>It only takes one nasty or disillusioned person to start a vicious rumour, and the snowball effect can be horrendous, particularly if the accusation is of a sexual nature.</p>
<p>Anyone can be maliciously targeted and even when innocent, their life can be tarred forever.</p>
<p>As Martel quite rightly says, a person is innocent until proven guilty. Let’s hope it stays that way. <strong>Peter Brady.</strong></p>
